{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":797,"text":"I'd like you to come back with me for a moment"},{"time":3451,"text":"to the 19th century,"},{"time":5475,"text":"specifically to June 24, 1833."},{"time":9923,"text":"The British Association for the Advancement of Science"},{"time":12978,"text":"is holding its third meeting at the University of Cambridge."},{"time":16769,"text":"It's the first night of the meeting,"},{"time":18980,"text":"and a confrontation is about to take place"},{"time":21843,"text":"that will change science forever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25451,"text":"An elderly, white-haired man stands up."},{"time":28428,"text":"The members of the Association are shocked to realize"},{"time":31890,"text":"that it's the poet Samuel Taylor Coleridge,"},{"time":34914,"text":"who hadn't even left his house in years until that day."},{"time":39874,"text":"They're even more shocked by what he says."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42770,"text":"\"You must stop calling yourselves natural philosophers.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":48206,"text":"Coleridge felt that true philosophers like himself"},{"time":51250,"text":"pondered the cosmos from their armchairs."},{"time":54298,"text":"They were not mucking around in the fossil pits"},{"time":56754,"text":"or conducting messy experiments with electrical piles"},{"time":60118,"text":"like the members of the British Association."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63090,"text":"The crowd grew angry and began to complain loudly."},{"time":67677,"text":"A young Cambridge scholar named William Whewell stood up"},{"time":71055,"text":"and quieted the audience."},{"time":73271,"text":"He politely agreed that an appropriate name"},{"time":76098,"text":"for the members of the association did not exist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79914,"text":"\"If 'philosophers' is taken to be too wide and lofty a term,\""},{"time":85458,"text":"he said, \"then, by analogy with 'artist,'"},{"time":90274,"text":"we may form 'scientist.'\""},{"time":94214,"text":"This was the first time the word scientist"},{"time":96843,"text":"was uttered in public,"},{"time":98697,"text":"only 179 years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102293,"text":"I first found out about this confrontation when I was in graduate school,"},{"time":105438,"text":"and it kind of blew me away."},{"time":107482,"text":"I mean, how could the word scientist"},{"time":109666,"text":"not have existed until 1833?"},{"time":113155,"text":"What were scientists called before?"},{"time":115346,"text":"What had changed to make a new name necessary"},{"time":118671,"text":"precisely at that moment?"},{"time":121801,"text":"Prior to this meeting, those who studied the natural world"},{"time":124895,"text":"were talented amateurs."},{"time":127067,"text":"Think of the country clergyman or squire"},{"time":129355,"text":"collecting his beetles or fossils,"},{"time":131868,"text":"like Charles Darwin, for example,"},{"time":134163,"text":"or, the hired help of a nobleman, like Joseph Priestley,"},{"time":138339,"text":"who was the literary companion"},{"time":140695,"text":"to the Marquis of Lansdowne"},{"time":142855,"text":"when he discovered oxygen."},{"time":145727,"text":"After this, they were scientists,"},{"time":148527,"text":"professionals with a particular scientific method,"},{"time":152361,"text":"goals, societies and funding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156096,"text":"Much of this revolution can be traced to four men"},{"time":159372,"text":"who met at Cambridge University in 1812:"},{"time":162631,"text":"Charles Babbage, John Herschel, Richard Jones and William Whewell."},{"time":167186,"text":"These were brilliant, driven men"},{"time":169663,"text":"who accomplished amazing things."},{"time":172935,"text":"Charles Babbage, I think known to most TEDsters,"},{"time":175934,"text":"invented the first mechanical calculator"},{"time":178729,"text":"and the first prototype of a modern computer."},{"time":182752,"text":"John Herschel mapped the stars of the southern hemisphere,"},{"time":186812,"text":"and, in his spare time, co-invented photography."},{"time":191042,"text":"I'm sure we could all be that productive"},{"time":193190,"text":"without Facebook or Twitter to take up our time."},{"time":196074,"text":"Richard Jones became an important economist"},{"time":199364,"text":"who later influenced Karl Marx."},{"time":201891,"text":"And Whewell not only coined the term scientist,"},{"time":205413,"text":"as well as the words anode, cathode and ion,"},{"time":209448,"text":"but spearheaded international big science"},{"time":212484,"text":"with his global research on the tides."},{"time":215580,"text":"In the Cambridge winter of 1812 and 1813,"},{"time":219292,"text":"the four met for what they called philosophical breakfasts."},{"time":223055,"text":"They talked about science"},{"time":224815,"text":"and the need for a new scientific revolution."},{"time":227937,"text":"They felt science had stagnated"},{"time":229828,"text":"since the days of the scientific revolution that had happened"},{"time":233080,"text":"in the 17th century."},{"time":235318,"text":"It was time for a new revolution,"},{"time":237384,"text":"which they pledged to bring about,"},{"time":239508,"text":"and what's so amazing about these guys is,"},{"time":242229,"text":"not only did they have these"},{"time":244012,"text":"grandiose undergraduate dreams,"},{"time":246605,"text":"but they actually carried them out,"},{"time":248845,"text":"even beyond their wildest dreams."},{"time":251893,"text":"And I'm going to tell you today"},{"time":252985,"text":"about four major changes to science these men made."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257942,"text":"About 200 years before,"},{"time":260365,"text":"Francis Bacon and then, later, Isaac Newton,"},{"time":263093,"text":"had proposed an inductive scientific method."},{"time":266805,"text":"Now that's a method that starts from"},{"time":269342,"text":"observations and experiments"},{"time":271797,"text":"and moves to generalizations about nature called natural laws,"},{"time":275269,"text":"which are always subject to revision or rejection"},{"time":277753,"text":"should new evidence arise."},{"time":280298,"text":"However, in 1809, David Ricardo muddied the waters"},{"time":285681,"text":"by arguing that the science of economics"},{"time":288630,"text":"should use a different, deductive method."},{"time":291779,"text":"The problem was that an influential group at Oxford"},{"time":295458,"text":"began arguing that because it worked so well in economics,"},{"time":299539,"text":"this deductive method ought to be applied"},{"time":302209,"text":"to the natural sciences too."},{"time":304883,"text":"The members of the philosophical breakfast club disagreed."},{"time":308539,"text":"They wrote books and articles promoting inductive method"},{"time":311821,"text":"in all the sciences"},{"time":313453,"text":"that were widely read by natural philosophers,"},{"time":316311,"text":"university students and members of the public."},{"time":319733,"text":"Reading one of Herschel's books"},{"time":321489,"text":"was such a watershed moment for Charles Darwin"},{"time":324279,"text":"that he would later say, \"Scarcely anything in my life"},{"time":328076,"text":"made so deep an impression on me."},{"time":330663,"text":"It made me wish to add my might"},{"time":333271,"text":"to the accumulated store of natural knowledge.\""},{"time":336799,"text":"It also shaped Darwin's scientific method,"},{"time":339911,"text":"as well as that used by his peers."},{"time":343770,"text":"[Science for the public good]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":345548,"text":"Previously, it was believed that scientific knowledge"},{"time":348142,"text":"ought to be used for the good of the king or queen,"},{"time":350775,"text":"or for one's own personal gain."},{"time":353688,"text":"For example, ship captains needed to know"},{"time":356391,"text":"information about the tides in order to safely dock at ports."},{"time":360578,"text":"Harbormasters would gather this knowledge"},{"time":362771,"text":"and sell it to the ship captains."},{"time":365787,"text":"The philosophical breakfast club changed that,"},{"time":368395,"text":"working together."},{"time":369745,"text":"Whewell's worldwide study of the tides"},{"time":371825,"text":"resulted in public tide tables and tidal maps"},{"time":374963,"text":"that freely provided the harbormasters' knowledge"},{"time":377950,"text":"to all ship captains."},{"time":380051,"text":"Herschel helped by making tidal observations"},{"time":382853,"text":"off the coast of South Africa,"},{"time":384821,"text":"and, as he complained to Whewell,"},{"time":387171,"text":"he was knocked off the docks during a violent high tide for his trouble."},{"time":392323,"text":"The four men really helped each other in every way."},{"time":395051,"text":"They also relentlessly lobbied the British government"},{"time":398363,"text":"for the money to build Babbage's engines"},{"time":400999,"text":"because they believed these engines"},{"time":402990,"text":"would have a huge practical impact on society."},{"time":406824,"text":"In the days before pocket calculators,"},{"time":409444,"text":"the numbers that most professionals needed --"},{"time":412780,"text":"bankers, insurance agents, ship captains, engineers â€”"},{"time":416388,"text":"were to be found in lookup books like this,"},{"time":419472,"text":"filled with tables of figures."},{"time":421868,"text":"These tables were calculated"},{"time":424276,"text":"using a fixed procedure over and over"},{"time":427195,"text":"by part-time workers known as -- and this is amazing -- computers,"},{"time":431864,"text":"but these calculations were really difficult."},{"time":434743,"text":"I mean, this nautical almanac"},{"time":436991,"text":"published the lunar differences for every month of the year."},{"time":440861,"text":"Each month required 1,365 calculations,"},{"time":445527,"text":"so these tables were filled with mistakes."},{"time":448511,"text":"Babbage's difference engine was the first mechanical calculator"},{"time":452676,"text":"devised to accurately compute any of these tables."},{"time":456655,"text":"Two models of his engine were built in the last 20 years"},{"time":460191,"text":"by a team from the Science Museum of London"},{"time":462951,"text":"using his own plans."},{"time":464634,"text":"This is the one now at the Computer History Museum in California,"},{"time":468772,"text":"and it calculates accurately. It actually works."},{"time":472479,"text":"Later, Babbage's analytical engine"},{"time":475094,"text":"was the first mechanical computer in the modern sense."},{"time":479379,"text":"It had a separate memory and central processor."},{"time":482333,"text":"It was capable of iteration, conditional branching"},{"time":485786,"text":"and parallel processing,"},{"time":487258,"text":"and it was programmable using punched cards,"},{"time":490230,"text":"an idea Babbage took from Jacquard's loom."},{"time":493702,"text":"Tragically, Babbage's engines never were built in his day"},{"time":497938,"text":"because most people thought that"},{"time":500125,"text":"non-human computers would have no usefulness"},{"time":503020,"text":"for the public."},{"time":504602,"text":"[New scientific institutions]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":506614,"text":"Founded in Bacon's time, the Royal Society of London"},{"time":510119,"text":"was the foremost scientific society in England"},{"time":513116,"text":"and even in the rest of the world."},{"time":515357,"text":"By the 19th century, it had become"},{"time":517822,"text":"a kind of gentleman's club"},{"time":519655,"text":"populated mainly by antiquarians, literary men and the nobility."},{"time":524662,"text":"The members of the philosophical breakfast club"},{"time":526815,"text":"helped form a number of new scientific societies,"},{"time":529829,"text":"including the British Association."},{"time":532229,"text":"These new societies required"},{"time":534612,"text":"that members be active researchers publishing their results."},{"time":538102,"text":"They reinstated the tradition of the Q&amp;A"},{"time":540942,"text":"after scientific papers were read,"},{"time":543212,"text":"which had been discontinued by the Royal Society"},{"time":545532,"text":"as being ungentlemanly."},{"time":548437,"text":"And for the first time, they gave women a foot in the door of science."},{"time":553333,"text":"Members were encouraged to bring their wives,"},{"time":555993,"text":"daughters and sisters to the meetings of the British Association,"},{"time":559919,"text":"and while the women were expected to attend"},{"time":562689,"text":"only the public lectures and the social events like this one,"},{"time":566530,"text":"they began to infiltrate the scientific sessions as well."},{"time":570639,"text":"The British Association would later be the first"},{"time":573523,"text":"of the major national science organizations in the world"},{"time":577167,"text":"to admit women as full members."},{"time":579872,"text":"[External funding for science]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":581313,"text":"Up to the 19th century,"},{"time":582708,"text":"natural philosophers were expected to pay"},{"time":585020,"text":"for their own equipment and supplies."},{"time":587333,"text":"Occasionally, there were prizes,"},{"time":589796,"text":"such as that given to John Harrison in the 18th century,"},{"time":593125,"text":"for solving the so-called longitude problem,"},{"time":596208,"text":"but prizes were only given after the fact,"},{"time":599053,"text":"when they were given at all."},{"time":600837,"text":"On the advice of the philosophical breakfast club,"},{"time":603741,"text":"the British Association began to use the extra money"},{"time":607052,"text":"generated by its meetings to give grants"},{"time":609726,"text":"for research in astronomy, the tides, fossil fish,"},{"time":612948,"text":"shipbuilding, and many other areas."},{"time":615775,"text":"These grants not only allowed"},{"time":617550,"text":"less wealthy men to conduct research,"},{"time":619893,"text":"but they also encouraged thinking outside the box,"},{"time":622829,"text":"rather than just trying to solve one pre-set question."},{"time":626902,"text":"Eventually, the Royal Society"},{"time":629301,"text":"and the scientific societies of other countries followed suit,"},{"time":632710,"text":"and this has become -- fortunately it's become --"},{"time":635574,"text":"a major part of the scientific landscape today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640324,"text":"So the philosophical breakfast club"},{"time":643338,"text":"helped invent the modern scientist."},{"time":646485,"text":"That's the heroic part of their story."},{"time":649713,"text":"There's a flip side as well."},{"time":652652,"text":"They did not foresee at least one consequence"},{"time":655636,"text":"of their revolution."},{"time":658172,"text":"They would have been deeply dismayed"},{"time":660548,"text":"by today's disjunction between science and the rest of culture."},{"time":665032,"text":"It's shocking to realize"},{"time":667689,"text":"that only 28 percent of American adults"},{"time":671029,"text":"have even a very basic level of science literacy,"},{"time":674580,"text":"and this was tested by asking simple questions like,"},{"time":677651,"text":"\"Did humans and dinosaurs inhabit the Earth at the same time?\""},{"time":681460,"text":"and \"What proportion of the Earth is covered in water?\""},{"time":686222,"text":"Once scientists became members of a professional group,"},{"time":690215,"text":"they were slowly walled off from the rest of us."},{"time":693580,"text":"This is the unintended consequence of the revolution"},{"time":697507,"text":"that started with our four friends."}]},{"cues":[{"time":700542,"text":"Charles Darwin said,"},{"time":702335,"text":"\"I sometimes think that general and popular treatises"},{"time":706420,"text":"are almost as important for the progress of science"},{"time":709189,"text":"as original work.\""},{"time":710776,"text":"In fact, \"Origin of Species\" was written"},{"time":713890,"text":"for a general and popular audience,"},{"time":715999,"text":"and was widely read when it first appeared."},{"time":719892,"text":"Darwin knew what we seem to have forgotten,"},{"time":723903,"text":"that science is not only for scientists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728322,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729943,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}